cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper discusses the use of GANs for image generation and improving the aesthetic quality of generated images through human interactions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as GANs are a popular topic in this field. The paper also focuses on image generation, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the use of human interactions to improve the generative model suggests a focus on human-computer interaction, which falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also involves the use of an auxiliary objective function, which is a common topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's focus on improving the aesthetic quality of generated images suggests a connection to cs.MM (Multimedia), which includes topics such as image and video processing.
